Basic Concept

An NMOS transistor controls current flow between the drain (D) and source (S) using the gate voltage (VGS).

VGS â†’ controls how strongly the channel conducts.

VDS â†’ controls how much voltage is dropped across the channel.

ID â†’ is the resulting drain current.

